==Records==
Tatsu is the world's tallest, fastest, and longest [[Flying roller coaster]] in the world. The roller coaster also holds the record for the highest [[Roller coaster elements#Pretzel loop|pretzel loop]] which is {{convert|124|ft|m|adj=off}} high and is the only Flying roller coaster to have a [[Roller coaster elements#Zero-gravity roll|zero-gravity roll]].<ref>{{cite web | title=Roller Coaster Search Results <U+2014> Flying coasters, sorted by height |publisher=Roller Coaster Database | url=http://rcdb.com/r.htm?nm=na&order=-23&de=4&ot=2 | accessdate=December 19, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=Roller Coaster Search Results <U+2014> Flying coasters, sorted by length |publisher=Roller Coaster Database | url=http://rcdb.com/r.htm?nm=na&order=-25&de=4&ot=2 | accessdate=December 19, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=Roller Coaster Search Results <U+2014> Flying coasters, sorted by speed |publisher=Roller Coaster Database | url=http://rcdb.com/r.htm?nm=na&order=-22&de=4&ot=2 | accessdate=December 19, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=Roller Coaster Search Results <U+2014> Flying coasters with zero-G roll |publisher=Roller Coaster Database | url=http://rcdb.com/r.htm?nm=na&el=8884&de=4&ot=2 | accessdate=December 19, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=Roller Coaster Search Results <U+2014> Flying coasters with Pretzel Loop, sorted by height | url=http://rcdb.com/r.htm?nm=na&el=8888&order=-23&de=4&ot=2 |publisher=Roller Coaster Database | accessdate=January 13, 2013}}</ref>

